<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
G-195 HIGH SPEDD NETWORKS: TECHNOLOGY AND BUSINESS TRENDS
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>G-195 HIGH SPEED NETWORDS: TECHNOLOGY AND BUSINESS
TRENDS
</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>ANAND V. RAO</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>


<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

This study was done with the objectives of identifying some of the leading technologies that are 
influencing the emerging high-speed networking industry and determine their growth
opportunities, 
prime product areas and the type of applications that lend themselves significantly to specific 
technologies.  The growth of high-speed networking industry has been influenced by several
factors that 
impact on its growth.  Some of these include the increasing use of multimedia, desktop
videoconferencing, 
high-volume data transfer, Internet connectivity, scientific and engineering applications, federal 
government supported applications, etc.  The unique nature of the applications used in these
environments 
lend themselves to be implemented on specific high-speed networking technologies.  This in turn
impacts 
on the services, type of networking and end-user products that are used in each technology area. 
One of 
the major goals of this study is to identify the growth opportunities for each type of technology as
a whole 
and also the products and applications that benefit the most from it.  The primary stated objective
of this 
study is to focus on overall opportunities in the U.S. and specific areas worldwide where
high-speed 
networking is on the rise.<P>


<B>REASONS FOR DOING THE STUDY</B><P>

This study provides a comparative analysis of growth opportunities in six technology areas that
are 
impacting on high-speed networking.  While studies performed by others focus on each area of
high-speed 
technology separately, this study offers a unique comparative analysis of six of the most discussed 
technology standards in the industry.  The study performs an analysis of each technology area
separately 
and then cross-references growth opportunities by each applications area and technology.  The
study aims 
to fill a major gap in the industry for an in-depth comparative analysis of major technologies that
are 
influencing the high-speed networking industry.  Additionally, this study presents the individual
and 
comparative growth opportunities for the six technology groups in easily understandable tabular
format.  
Our prestudy research with various industry sources indicated that there is a need for a
comparative 
growth study for major technologies and applications groups, which inspired this effort.<P>


<B>CONTRIBUTION OF THE STUDY AND FOR WHOM</B><P>

This study contributes a unique perspective of the emerging high-speed networking industry and
presents 
a comprehensive growth study for the benefit of individuals and organizations involved in various
areas of 
the industry.  While highly focused studies available in the industry highlight developments in a
product 
or technology area, this study specializes in focusing on comparative analysis that should be of
special 
appeal to product and applications developers, consultants, hardware and software engineers,
phone 
companies, service providers and others.  This study contributes a comparative analysis of U.S.
and 
international markets hitherto not attempted in the industry.<P>


<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

The study includes an analysis of six major technology areas that are considered the most
discussed 
standards in the industry and aims to provide a brief analysis of each technology, its unique
features, 
advantages and disadvantages, business and technology trends that are influencing the technology
and the 
industry as a whole, main products, applications and services in each technology area and presents
growth 
analysis till the year 2001 in tabular and chart formats.  Additional analysis highlights the most 
productive end-user areas where the technologies are applied.<P>

The format of the study includes the presentation of the most relevant topics in each technology
by 
products, services and applications in a descriptive fashion and presents the growth data in easily 
understandable tabular formats, where applicable percentage average annual growth rates for
products, 
services and applications are presented.<P>   

Additionally, where appropriate, specific end-user products and their relevance to the technology
and 
growth projections are also presented.<P>  


<B>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

This study presents an analysis by each major technology, product, services and applications
groups by 
segment, focusing on the significant developments that influence the industry.  Where appropriate, 
separate tables depict growth projections in dollar value as well as in units for each product.  
Internationally, comprehensive growth rates by technology in main geographical areas such as
Europe, the 
Far East, Asia and India and South America are presented in tabular format.  A comparative
analysis of 
growth of major high-speed technologies in the U.S. and the rest of the world is also
presented.<P>




<B>INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

This study was conducted by direct interviews of industry executives and important individuals
connected 
with associations, standards bodies, consulting houses and systems integration agencies, as well as 
collection of data from industry publications, databases, standards bodies, published reports from 
universities, government agencies and research organizations, etc.  Over 100 individuals were
contacted 
and data was gathered through telephone interviews and hard copy surveys.<P>

Users were contacted to elicit information on their preference for technology, problems they face
in 
implementation, likely additions that they plan to their facilities using specific technologies,
etc.<P>  





