<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
G-067X: PRINTED CIRCUIT BOARDS: 
MARKETS & OPPORTUNITIES
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>G-067X: PRINTED CIRCUIT BOARDS: 
MARKETS & OPPORTUNITIES
</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>Richard Hilton
</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOALS AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

Printed Circuit Boards presents a detailed view of market size,
growth, and trends for this industry.  The major product lines and
applications are identified and the market size for each product
line and application are estimated for the next five years. 
Significant technological trends and developments in materials and
applications are identified and analyzed.  International aspects of
the printed circuit board market are discussed, and the structure
of the industry is addressed, including profiles of the major
printed circuit board suppliers.<P>


<b>REASONS FOR DOING THE REPORT</B><P>

Printed circuit boards represent a technology critical to modern
electronic products.  The growth of the electronic equipment
industry is driven by a seemingly insatiable demand for both new
and existing products.  High definition television, interactive
multimedia, handheld computers, voice recognition synthesis, image
processing, character recognition, and artificial intelligence will
enter the market later this decade.  Coupled with existing radio,
television, computer, and other products, these new technologies
will demand great quantities of sophisticated electronic equipment
and components, including printed circuit boards.<P>


<b>CONTRIBUTION OF THE REPORT AND FOR WHOM</B><P>

This BCC report provides in-depth information and state-of-the art
technological evaluations for decision making by those involved in,
or considering becoming involved in, the supply of printed circuit
boards to the computer, communications, instrumentation,
industrial, consumer, automotive, and military markets.<P>

The study can assist clients in strategic planning, acquisition
analysis, technology analysis, commercial development of new
products, and analysis of competitors' strategies, strengths,
weaknesses, pricing, market share, and profitability.<P>


<b>SCOPE AND FORMAT OF THE REPORT</B><P>

This report analyzes the products, applications, technology,
international aspects, and industry structure.  It also profiles
key companies/organizations involved in the supply of printed
circuit boards to the computer, communications, instrumentation,
industrial, consumer, automotive, and military markets.<P>

The format of this report is to state all values, projections, and
forecasts in terms of constant dollars unless otherwise noted.  All
numbers and projections are substantiated or noted as to their
origin.<P>


<b>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

The background research of Printed Circuit Boards consisted of a
thorough analysis of trade, government, and company literature, and
the substantial information in BCC's database.  An extensive series
of personal and telephone interviews with key executives and
officials in the industries, trade associations, and government
followed the background work.  The expert and reasoned comments of
these people, combined with BCC experience and analysis, provide
the basis for the content of this report.<P>

The market growth for printed circuit boards forecast in this
report is somewhat more optimistic than that of some other
contemporary forecasts.  BCC believes that growth in electronics,
particularly portable electronics, and resultant demand for
miniaturization, high connection and wiring densities, and high pin
counts, will fuel a more robust printed circuit board market than
would otherwise be expected.  The contents of the report amplify
these considerations.<P>


<b>INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

Major sources of information are noted throughout the report and in
Appendix A (Works Cited).<P>


<b>BCC CREDENTIALS</B><P>

The author of this report has worked on many assignments dealing
with the supply of technologically advanced materials to industry,
and has analytical familiarity with many of the important issues
influencing the supply of printed circuit boards to the computer,
communications, instrumentation, industrial, consumer, automotive,
and military markets.<P>



