<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
GB-128R THICK AND THIN FILMS IN MICROELECTRONICS
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>GB-128R THICK AND THIN FILMS IN MICROELECTRONICS
</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>ROBERT MORAN</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

BCC's goal in conducting this study was to determine the current
status of the market for thick and thin film materials in the
microelectronics industry, and assess their growth potential over
an eight year period from 1992 to 2000, the end of the century.  We
also looked at their growth positions at the end of five years,
1997, the more traditional time frame for market studies.<P>

Our major objective was to present a comprehensive analysis of the
current thick and thin film materials market for microelectronic
products and plot its future course.<P>

<B>REASONS FOR DOING THIS STUDY</B><P>

Thick films provide high volume and low cost yields while thin film
deposition and reaction techniques make it possible to engineer
materials on the atomic scale.  There is a convergence of both
technologies in today's microelectronics market.  Thick and thin
film material technologies are being developed and evaluated by the
worldwide electronics industry because they offer solutions to many
of the advanced device challenges relating to high density and
greater speed of current and future electronic devices.<P>

BCC decided to examine the current status of thick and thin film
technologies.  We were interested in how they were evolving and
what specific changes were taking place.<P>

<B>CONTRIBUTIONS TO THE STUDY AND FOR WHOM</B><P>

We assembled a study of the two technologies: thick and thin film.
We present a worldwide industry structure, examine the competitive
aspects of the microelectronics and materials industries, analyze
the current markets, identify factors that will drive demand, and
project shipments to 1997 and 2000.  The application of thick and
thin films to semiconductor and related devices, and components, is
analyzed.  This study will be of interest to electronic material
suppliers, manufacturers of semiconductors and related devices such
as hybrid circuits and multichip modules, makers of electronic
components, suppliers of printed circuit boards, and manufacturers
of electrical and electronic equipment.<P>


<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

The scope of our study encompasses thick and thin film materials
and technologies in terms of processes, properties and
applications.  Trends in demand for microelectronic products are
reviewed and their impact on film technologies is assessed.
Semiconductor and component applications of thick and thin films
are discussed and future market drivers are identified.  Materials
are analyzed by their basic functions as conductors, resistors and
dielectrics.   Specific material properties are reviewed and sample
configurations of thick and thin film products are provided.  The
value of material shipments is projected by basic function, type of
material, and application.  Technological issues and trends are
reviewed.  Other influential factors such as the economic climate
are also discussed.<P>

Because this is a worldwide industry, BCC analyzes the domestic and
international legislative issues, standards situations and their
impact on the microelectronics materials business.  BCC also
presents an analysis of market factors within the thick and thin
film industries and among various end-user industries, and looks at
their impact on the future.<P>

<B>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

BCC presents an analysis of the value of thick and thin film
material shipments by major categories.  Our estimated value is
what manufacturers and material providers have paid in current
dollars.   Then, based on our surveys, we analyze thick and thin
film materials by basic function, type of material and application,
calculate estimates for growth, and forecast value of shipments for
1997 and 2000.<P>

<B>INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

BCC surveyed approximately 70 companies to obtain the data for this
report.  Included were manufacturers of semiconductors, components,
thick and thin film materials, coating service providers, materials
distributors, and industrial and consumer electronic companies.
Additional data for this report were obtained from government
information, trade associations, industry and financial sources,
and an exhaustive review of technical papers.<P>

<B>RELATED BCC WORK CREDENTIALS</B><P>

Several other BCC reports are related to this topic.  They are:<P>
 
<UL>GB-156 Advanced Electronics Packaging Systems Technology Through
2000<BR> 
GB-148 Electronic Connector Materials<BR> 
GB-138 "Multichip Modules (MCMs) in Electronics: Materials, Processes, Applications<BR>
G-118 Surface Mount Technology in Electronics<BR> 
GB-131 "Conformal Coatings in the Global Electronics Industry<BR> 
G-067U "The Printed Circuit Board Industry<BR>
G-122 "Fine Pitch Technology</UL><P>
Also available from BCC are two monthly newsletters that cover
electronic materials and optics: "Electronic Materials Technology
News" and "Optical Materials and Engineering News."<P>

