<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
 C-023U  THE CHANGING NONO-ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGE MARKETS:
                       TRADITIONAL VERSUS NICHES</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2> C-023U  THE CHANGING NONO-ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGE MARKETS:
                       TRADITIONAL VERSUS NICHES</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>SAUL ESTREICHER</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

The purpose of this report is to: 1)  update the previous Beverage
Industry: Markets, Players and Packaging Trends study published by
BCC in 1987.  BCC has been following trends in the beverage
industry over time and this report represents the third one
published since 1980; 2) identify, quantify and analyze the market
for non-alcoholic beverages and 3) expand on the previous study by
looking at the latest trends over the past 5 years and determine
where new product growth may come from in this industry.  The
report presents a comprehensive overview of the changing beverage
industry and an outlook for where it may be heading.<P>

It covers 8 non-alcoholic beverages in some detail with a brief
overview of alcoholic beverages and their niches.  In addition to
trends in the traditional markets, new product and existing niches
are analyzed to determine their history and viability within each
of the 9 beverage industries including alcoholic beverages.<P>

<B>REASONS FOR DOING THE STUDY</B><P>

The report brings together and analyzes data and makes forecasts
for all the major beverages consumed in the United States and
compares one with the other.  It analyses sales, growth and 5 year
forecasts for all major beverages consumed in the U.S. including
1991 projections and 1996 forecasts.<P>

We present consumption patterns; production; who's doing what and
why; packaging information; ingredient analysis focused on sugar
substitutes; channels of distribution; advertising data;
demographics; the major players, their brands, market share and
what they're doing; flavor preferences; new products; beverage
niches and import data.  In this way industry analysts can have
most of the pertinent decision making data and information as well
as forecasts on beverages under one cover.<P>

<B>CONTRIBUTION OF THE STUDY AND TARGET AUDIENCE</B><P>

The study serves as an overview of the non-alcoholic beverage
industry, its history and 5 year trends.  It emphasizes key niche
markets within each of the major beverage categories to illustrate
where the mature industry is heading.  The report brings together
data sources on each category under one cover for industry analysts
to use as a handy reference.  Product managers, investors, bankers,
researchers, Wall Street analysts and business libraries with
interests in the beverage industry will find this volume useful to
assess specific beverage product categories and its prospects.   It is recommended for marketing, sales, strategic planning, product
and corporate development  planning and top management in small,
medium or large companies.<P>

<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

The scope of this study includes but is not limited to the major
product groupings mass marketed primarily through the supermarket.
The products include carbonated soft drinks, juice and juice
drinks, powdered drinks, bottled water, coffee, tea and  milk.
Such products included are alcoholic beverage niches like wine
coolers and non-alcoholic beer.  Other channels of importance like
vending and foodservice are covered.<P>

The products chosen for coverage are the ones which follow the
latest trends in health and diet orientation, the direction in
which the beverage market is heading along with other food
products.  However, caffeinated products including soda, coffee and
tea are included: alcoholic products are summarized to round out
the picture of the beverage industry and to examine the
health-oriented trends that are drawing attention to and affecting
the alcoholic beverage industry.<P>

The report covers the following 12 beverage niche categories:<P>
<PRE>
<B>    BEVERAGE                             NICHES</B><BR>
Carbonated Soft Drinks                      All Natural Soft Drinks
Ground Coffee and Instant                   Ready-to-Drink Iced coffee
                                            Gourmet Coffee
Tea Bags, Bulk and Instant                  Ready-to-Drink Iced Tea
Bottled Water                               Flavored Waters
Fruit Juices}                               Sparkling Juices
Fruit Drinks}                               Isotonic Drinks
Powdered Drink Mixes                        Isotonic Powdered Beverages
Milk                                        Ready-to-Drink Meal
Replacements
                                            Specialty Diet/Health Milks
Alcoholic Drinks
      Wine                                  Wine Coolers and Diet Wines
      Distilled spirits                     Light Distilled Spirits, Mixed
Drinks
                                            Light Spirits
      Malt Beverages                        Low Alcohol and Non-Alcoholic beer</PRE>

<B>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

Research for The Changing Non-Alcoholic Beverage Market industry
survey consisted of extensive secondary research and conversations
with industry representatives.  Primary research was conducted by
phone interviews.<P>

Data are standardized regarding definition of the markets and
products to ensure consistency of findings.<P>


<B>INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

Extensive literature searches were done drawing on publicly
available sources including trade association, trade journals,
company communications, government documents and private research
studies.  Direct company information was obtained wherever
possible.  Sources contacted include manufacturers, distributors,
advertising/PR agencies, trade associations and journal and
newsletter editors.<P>

